            <b><font color="#000099" face="Arial" size="4">Moderator Comment</font></b>
            <FONT
            face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color=#000099 size=+1>
            <HR>
            </FONT>
            <P><b><a name="mod"><font face="arial" color="#ff0000" size="2"></font></a><font face="arial" color="#ff0000" size="2">Web Development in 2003</font></b>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Happy New Year I-Developers,</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">I hope the festive season has
            provided the opportunity for you all to energize the batteries in
            readiness for the year of coding ahead :)</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">2002 zipped by so quickly that I
            think it did little more than set the stage for some interesting
            issues that should generate some fun in 2003. One area in particular
            is the Web Application User Interface development environment, where
            Flash MX, SVG, XForms, XUL and Curl (as technologies) are all
            positioning themselves for a share of the action. An interesting
            observation is that Microsoft has not yet shown it's hand...Will MS
            purchase Macromedia and promote Flash as the rumours suggest?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Another big, albeit ongoing, issue
            for this year will be in the Web Service arena. Perhaps we will see
            the emergence of useful applications built on the WSDL, SOAP and
            UDDI architecture.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">What issues do you think will be big
            in 2003?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">&gt;&gt;</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">To kick this year's discussion off, I
            can't think of a better post than the one sent by former moderator
            Rajesh Chawla. Rajesh asks the group to share its web service and
            SOAP experience.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Happy coding,<br>
            Peter Schonefeld<br>
            Web Developer<br>
            <a href="http://digitalcraft.com.au">http://digitalcraft.com.au</a>&nbsp;</font></p>
            <P><font face="Arial" size="2">Adventive<br>
            The Internet Knowledge Exchange<br>
            <a href="http://www.adventive.com">http://www.adventive.com</a></font>
